name: Chicken Curry
instructions: Heat oil in a pan. Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown. Add minced garlic and ginger paste, and cook for 2 minutes. Add tomato puree and cook until the oil separates. Add turmeric, cumin powder, coriander powder, and salt. Mix well. Add chicken pieces and coat them with the masala. Cook for 10 minutes on medium heat. Add 1 cup of water, cover, and simmer until the chicken is tender. Sprinkle garam masala and garnish with fresh coriander. Serve hot with rice or naan.

name: Spaghetti Carbonara
instructions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup of pasta water. In a pan, sauté pancetta until crispy. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. In a bowl, whisk eggs and Parmesan cheese. Add cooked spaghetti to the pan and toss. Remove from heat and quickly stir in the egg mixture, adding reserved pasta water to create a creamy sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Garnish with parsley and serve immediately.

name: Beef Tacos
instructions: Heat oil in a pan. Add chopped onion and garlic, and sauté until soft. Add ground beef and cook until browned. Add diced bell pepper and taco seasoning. Stir well and cook for 5 minutes. Warm taco shells in the oven. Fill each shell with the beef mixture. Top with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, cheese, and a dollop of sour cream. Serve immediately.

name: Vegetable Stir-Fry
instructions: Heat vegetable oil in a wok. Add minced garlic and ginger, and sauté for 1 minute. Add broccoli, bell pepper, carrot, and snap peas. Stir-fry for 5-7 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp. Add soy sauce, oyster sauce, and sesame oil. Toss to coat. Serve hot with steamed rice or noodles.

name: Classic Pancakes
instructions: In a bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt. In another bowl, mix milk, egg, melted butter, and vanilla extract. Combine wet and dry ingredients until just mixed. Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown. Serve with maple syrup and butter.

name: Chicken Alfredo Pasta
instructions: Cook fettuccine according to package instructions. In a pan, melt butter and sauté minced garlic. Add chicken slices and cook until browned. Pour in heavy cream and bring to a simmer. Stir in Parmesan cheese until melted. Add cooked pasta and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Garnish with parsley and serve hot.

name: Beef Burger
ingredients: Lettuce, tomato, and cheese for topping
instructions: In a bowl, mix ground beef, onion, egg, breadcrumbs, garlic powder, paprika, salt, and pepper. Form into patties. Heat a grill or pan and cook patties for 4-5 minutes on each side. Toast burger buns. Assemble burgers with lettuce, tomato, cheese, and patties. Serve with fries.

name: Vegetable Soup
instructions: Heat olive oil in a pot. Add onion, carrots, and celery, and sauté for 5 minutes. Add potato, green beans, vegetable broth, thyme, and rosemary. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Serve hot with crusty bread.

name: Chocolate Cake
instructions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Add eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla extract. Mix until smooth. Stir in boiling water. Pour batter into a greased cake pan. Bake for 30-35 minutes. Let cool before frosting.

name: Grilled Salmon
instructions: Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Brush salmon fillets with olive oil. Season with garlic, dill, salt, and pepper. Place lemon slices on top. Grill for 4-5 minutes on each side. Serve with a side of roasted vegetables.

name: Garlic Butter Shrimp
instructions: Melt butter in a pan over medium heat. Add minced garlic and sauté for 1 minute. Add shrimp, paprika, salt, and pepper. Cook for 2-3 minutes per side until pink and opaque. Drizzle with lemon juice and sprinkle with parsley. Serve hot.

name: Caprese Salad
instructions: Arrange tomato and mozzarella slices alternately on a plate. Tuck basil leaves in between. Drizzle with olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Season with salt and pepper. Serve fresh.

name: Lemon Herb Grilled Chicken
instructions: In a bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt, and pepper. Marinate chicken in the mixture for 30 minutes. Grill over medium-high heat for 6-7 minutes per side until fully cooked. Serve hot.

name: Greek Salad
instructions: In a large bowl, combine cucumber, tomato, red onion, feta cheese, and olives. Drizzle with olive oil and lemon juice. Sprinkle with oregano, salt, and pepper. Toss well and serve.

name: Stuffed Bell Peppers
instructions: Cut the tops off the bell peppers and remove seeds. In a pan, cook ground beef with onion and garlic until browned. Add rice, tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper. Stuff the mixture into the bell peppers. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 180°C for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

name: Chicken Parmesan
instructions: Preheat oven to 200°C. Dip chicken breasts into the beaten egg, then coat with a mixture of breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese. Heat olive oil in a pan and brown the chicken on both sides. Place chicken in a baking dish, top with marinara sauce and mozzarella cheese. Bake for 20 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and cheese is melted. Serve hot.

name: Mushroom Risotto
instructions: In a pan, melt butter and sauté onion and garlic until soft. Add sliced mushrooms and cook until tender. Add Arborio rice and cook for 1-2 minutes. Gradually add warm chicken broth, stirring constantly until absorbed. Once the rice is creamy and cooked through, stir in Parmesan cheese. Season with salt and pepper and serve.

name: Shrimp Tacos
instructions: Heat olive oil in a pan. Toss shrimp with cumin, paprika, chili powder, and lime juice. Cook shrimp in the pan for 2-3 minutes per side until pink. Warm the tortillas, then assemble tacos with shrimp, shredded lettuce, a dollop of sour cream, and fresh cilantro. Serve with extra lime wedges.

name: Pasta Primavera
instructions: Cook pasta according to package instructions. In a pan, heat olive oil and sauté garlic for 1 minute. Add zucchini, bell pepper, and cherry tomatoes. Cook until vegetables are tender. Toss the cooked pasta with the vegetables and Parmesan cheese. Season with salt and pepper and serve.

name: Beef Stew
instructions: In a pot, brown the beef stew meat. Add onions and garlic and cook until soft. Sprinkle with flour and stir for 1 minute. Add beef broth, tomato paste, carrots, and potatoes. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1-1.5 hours until beef is tender. Season with salt, pepper, and garnish with fresh parsley.

name: Fish Tacos
instructions: Season the fish fillets with paprika, garlic powder, lime juice, salt, and pepper. Cook the fish in a pan for 3-4 minutes per side. Warm the tortillas, then assemble tacos with fish, shredded cabbage, a dollop of sour cream, and fresh cilantro.

name: Eggplant Parmesan
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C. Dip eggplant slices into beaten eggs, then coat with breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese. Fry eggplant slices in olive oil until golden brown. Place in a baking dish, top with marinara sauce and mozzarella cheese. Bake for 20 minutes until cheese is melted. Serve hot.

name: Chicken Fajitas
instructions: Heat olive oil in a pan. Add chicken and cook until browned. Add onion and bell pepper, and cook until softened. Sprinkle with cumin, chili powder, paprika, salt, and pepper. Warm the tortillas and assemble fajitas with the chicken and vegetables. Serve with toppings like sour cream and salsa.

name: Pork Schnitzel
instructions: Flatten the pork chops using a meat mallet. Dip in flour, then beaten eggs, and coat with breadcrumbs. Heat oil in a pan and fry pork chops until golden brown on both sides. Serve with lemon wedges.

name: Vegetarian Chili
instructions: In a pot, sauté onions and garlic until soft. Add bell pepper and cook for 2 minutes. Add the beans, diced tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, salt, and pepper. Pour in vegetable broth and bring to a boil. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve hot with cornbread.

name: Chicken Shawarma
instructions: In a bowl, mix olive oil, cumin, paprika, garlic powder, turmeric, cinnamon, salt, and pepper. Coat the chicken thighs with the spice mixture and marinate for at least 1 hour. Cook the chicken in a pan or grill for 6-7 minutes per side until fully cooked. Warm the pita breads, then assemble shawarmas with sliced chicken, fresh parsley, and drizzle with tahini sauce.

name: Baked Ziti
instructions: Preheat oven to 180°C. Cook ziti pasta according to package instructions. In a pan, sauté onions and garlic in olive oil. Add marinara sauce, oregano, salt, and pepper. In a large baking dish, combine cooked pasta, ricotta cheese, marinara sauce mixture, and half of the mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Top with remaining mozzarella and Parmesan. Bake for 20-25 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.

name: Sweet and Sour Chicken
instructions: In a pan, heat vegetable oil and sauté chicken until browned. Add onions, bell pepper, and pineapple chunks. In a separate bowl, mix soy sauce, vinegar, ketchup, and sugar. Pour the sauce over the chicken and vegetables, and cook for 5 minutes. Mix cornstarch with water to thicken the sauce, then stir into the pan. Serve hot with rice.

name: Fettuccine Alfredo
instructions: Cook fettuccine according to package instructions. In a pan, melt butter and sauté garlic for 1 minute. Add heavy cream and bring to a simmer. Stir in Parmesan cheese and cook until smooth. Add cooked fettuccine and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Garnish with fresh parsley and serve hot.

name: Ratatouille
instructions: Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, sauté until fragrant. Add eggplant and cook for a few minutes. Stir in bell peppers, zucchini, and tomatoes. Season with thyme, salt, and pepper. Cover and simmer for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Garnish with fresh basil and serve warm.
